[VS2-338] DPO delivery tracker

Background:
DPO Officers need to monitor the delivery of approved Studies through Role-based Access Model (ROAM) to ensure timely data availability and identify potential risks or dependencies. No visibility into delivery progress makes it difficult to manage these processes effectively. This tracking capability enables DPO Officers to proactively manage dependencies, identify delivery risks, track completion rates, and ensure approved Studies are delivered through appropriate sources.

User Story:
As a DPO Officer, I want visibility of Open Access delivery so that that dependencies and risks are managed.

Acceptance criteria:
GIVEN a collection of approved Studies WHEN checking its status THEN track record of each individual Study is enabled.
GIVEN a collection of approved Studies WHEN checking track records THEN each method availability (e.g. available in PDP) is enabled.
GIVEN a collection of approved Studies WHEN particular availability method is not present THEN a mechanism to submit a request the addition is present.
GIVEN a Study availability method WHEN tracking status is viewed THEN the count of studies that have been added and those are pending are present.
GIVEN a collection of approved Studies WHEN checking its delivery progress THEN a report showing completed and uncompleted Study deliveries is present.